      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ULTIMATE MIKI (11) has been terrific in winning his three starts at this circuit and distance since switching from NSW, racing wide early before finding the front and scoring by 7.6m last week. Draws on the back row but came from this barrier for a tough win two back. Can do it again. BETTORS PRIDE (8) has been racing well of late. Came from the back row for fourth at his latest appearance. Has to contend with a wide draw but came from this barrier for third at G3 level two back at this circuit and distance. Big chance. A LITTLE SILENCE NZ (5) is hard to knock having yet to miss the top-two in Perth, last week coming from the back row to go under by only 2.3m. DARK EYES (2) showed pleasing improvement last time out when third at this circuit and distance and is aided by a lower draw.",
